# Network Configuration Lab: Cisco Packet Tracer

This repository contains the documentation and configuration steps for three fundamental networking practicals conducted in Cisco Packet Tracer.

## I. Peer-to-Peer Communication

**Objective:** Establishing a direct link between two workstations using physical media and manual address assignment.

### Hardware & Connectivity

* **Media:** Ethernet Crossover Cable.


* **Nodes:** 2 x Generic Host PCs.



### Configuration Parameters

| Device ID | IPv4 Address | Subnet Mask |
| --- | --- | --- |
| PC-A | 10.10.10.1 | 255.255.255.0 |
| PC-B | 10.10.10.2 | 255.255.255.0 |

> 

### Connectivity Test

To verify the connection, execute the following command from the PC-A terminal:

```bash
ping 10.10.10.2

```

---

## II. Centralized Switching (LAN)

**Objective:** Constructing a Local Area Network (LAN) utilizing a centralized Layer 2 switch to facilitate multi-node communication.

### Topology Components

* **Switching Fabric:** Cisco Catalyst 2960 Series.


* **Nodes:** 4 x Generic Host PCs.


* **Connectivity:** Cross-over cables (Note: Standard practice usually utilizes Straight-through cables for PC-to-Switch).



### Addressing Table

| Host Name | Static IP Address | Subnet Mask |
| --- | --- | --- |
| PC-1 | 10.1.1.1 | 255.255.255.0 |
| PC-2 | 10.1.1.2 | 255.255.255.0 |
| PC-3 | 10.1.1.3 | 255.255.255.0 |
| PC-4 | 10.1.1.5 | 255.255.255.0 |

> 

