## III. Inter-Subnet Routing Configuration

**Objective:** Utilizing a Layer 3 Router to bridge two distinct logical subnets, enabling cross-network data flow via Gateway interfaces.

### Network Infrastructure

* **Router:** Cisco 2911 Integrated Services Router (ISR).


* **Switching:** 2 x Cisco 2960 Switches.


* **Subnets:**
* **Subnet A:** 192.168.0.0/24 (Gateway: Gi0/1).


* **Subnet B:** 192.168.10.0/24 (Gateway: Gi0/2).





### Device Configurations

| Subnet | Host | IP Address | Default Gateway |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **192.168.0.x** | PC-S1-A | 192.168.0.2 | 192.168.0.1 |
|  | PC-S1-B | 192.168.0.3 | 192.168.0.1 |
| **192.168.10.x** | PC-S2-A | 192.168.10.2 | 192.168.10.1 |
|  | PC-S2-B | 192.168.10.3 | 192.168.10.1 |

> 

### Router CLI Implementation

```ios
! Accessing Privilege Mode and Configuration
Router> enable
Router# configure terminal

! Configuring GigabitEthernet 0/1 (Subnet A)
Router(config)# interface g0/1
Router(config-if)# ip address 192.168.0.1 255.255.255.0
Router(config-if)# no shutdown
Router(config-if)# exit

! Configuring GigabitEthernet 0/2 (Subnet B)
Router(config)# interface g0/2
Router(config-if)# ip address 192.168.10.1 255.255.255.0
Router(config-if)# no shutdown
Router(config-if)# exit

! Saving Configuration to NVRAM
Router(config)# exit
Router# write memory

```

### Cross-Network Verification

Test reachability from a host in Subnet A to a host in Subnet B:

```bash
ping 192.168.10.2

```

